You're not crazy, I see these effects too. As I bring my hand closer to the camera (streaming colourised depth on D415), the camera first 'blacks out' my hand at say 25cm, then if I move it closer still (to <20cm) it goes all speckly with patches of different colours on my hand. If I mouseover these patches it returns a variety of distances, 0.5m, 1m etc. This happens even if I put the clamp on. My hand will go black sooner because the camera sees it as too close, then when I move it closer it will light up again because it thinks the depth values are legit and greater than the clamp.
To partially get around this, we recognise when the subject first goes out of range, or gets too close to the near extreme, and tell the user to move backwards. Doesn't help if the user starts off too close though!

