Would it be possible to rework this design so that we use the following metadata:

```protobuf
message ImagePluginData {
  tensorflow.TensorProto type = 1;
  int32 encoding = 2;
}
```

The `encoding` field would always be `10` for PNG, since go/tensorbase-design already allocates 0..9.

The `type` field would only have its metadata fields set: `dtype` and `tensor_shape`. It is used to communicate the shape that all the byte string tensors will take after they're run through png_decode. Within a given tag, they must all have the same dtype and shape. I suggest using `TensorProto` for this purpose, since it's less code and more easily merging protobufs might be useful.

